the Name=20
  Game&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3&amp;gt;Playing the Name=20
  Game&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;Those who may have stumbled across this blog in =
the=20
  hours since its &amp;lt;a=20
  =
href=3D"http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/BlunderDome/wingnut/2004/06/inaugur=
ation.asp"&amp;gt;inauguration&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;=20
  will notice that the Title and Description of the blog have changed=20
  already.&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;That =
is=20
  certainly consistent with what you should expect from this=20
  place.&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br=20
  /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Many a Slip Twixt Cup and=20
  Lip&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;.&amp;amp;nbsp; Of course there is no =
syndication=20
  feed button on the post pages yet, so that is something to be dealt =
with right=20
  away.&amp;amp;nbsp; Meanwhile, the really weird bots will have scraped =
it off=20
  the page by means &amp;lt;a=20
  href=3D"http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless/"&amp;gt;Prof.=20
  v.Clueless&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; may be tempted to look into, so let's say =
no more=20
  about that.&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br =
/&amp;gt;The other=20
  thing I need to record is that, on my Blogger Dashboard, it says this =
blog has=20
  no posts.&amp;amp;nbsp; Funny, it's right there.&amp;amp;nbsp; Been =
there for=20
  18 hours or so.&amp;amp;nbsp; The tricky part is imagining how that =
could even=20
  not work.&amp;amp;nbsp; That is not the kind of experience I intend to =

  promote, and it is a problem not-of-my-creation that I feel no =
obligation to=20
  fix.&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;You will =
notice=20
  that, for now, titles of postings appear multiple times.&amp;amp;nbsp; =
Once as=20
  the title of the posting and more times as a heading incorporated in =
the body=20
  of the posting itself.&amp;amp;nbsp; For example, there are, at the =
moment,=20
  three identical titles on this blog post.&amp;amp;nbsp; This is an =
incoherence=20
  case, and il Professor will definitely want to dig into that.=20
  &amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br=20
  /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Uh, you were talking about the naming =
of this=20
  place?&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp; I suppose there could be =
some=20
  exotic question for a future geek-trivia East-West superbowl about the =

  original name for this blog.&amp;amp;nbsp; Shh. Here's the=20
  secret.&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;The =
original=20
  title was &amp;lt;em&amp;gt;Spanner Wingnut's [Incredible [Secret]] =
Web=20
  Cellar&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt;.&amp;amp;nbsp; The Incredible was meant as =
homage to=20
  Don Tarbell (and his &amp;lt;a=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.tinaja.com/ismm01.html"&amp;gt;&amp;lt;em&amp;gt;Incre=
dible=20
  Secret Money =
Machine&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;).&amp;amp;nbsp; The=20
  Cellar was for &amp;lt;a=20
  =
href=3D"http:www.circuitcellar.com/magazine/staff.htm"&amp;gt;&amp;lt;em&=
amp;gt;Steve=20
  Ciarcia's Circuit =
Cellar&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;amp;nbsp;=20
  "Secret" never made it and "Incredible" disappeared between the =
initial site=20
  setup and customization of the setup information before the first=20
  post.&amp;amp;nbsp; And "Web Cellar" was too much of a stretch and I =
felt=20
  awkward with it, but I tried it out anyhow. "Muddleware" entered my =
thoughts=20
  in another context.&amp;amp;nbsp; I have already used it (as &amp;lt;a =

  =
href=3D"http://miser-theory.info/astraendo/pn/2004/06/fine-kettle-of-fish=
.asp"&amp;gt;middle=20
  muddle&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;), and I intend to expand on =
that.&amp;amp;nbsp; The=20
  resonance with the bumblingness of this particular blog adventure was=20
  irresistable.&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;#13;&amp;lt;br =
/&amp;gt;For=20
  now, the name 's a keeper. -- &amp;lt;a=20
  =
href=3D"http://orcmid.com/construction/orcmid.htm"&amp;gt;&amp;lt;em&amp;=
gt;orcmid&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;=20
